<topic id="kindle-transformation-output">
  <title>DITA Map Kindle Transformation</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Transformation Scenarios<indexterm>DITA Map to Kindle</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>DITA Map to Kindle transformation </indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p id="p_nbl_cgk_54b">To produce Kindle books from DITA XML content, follow these steps:<ol
        id="ol_obl_cgk_54b">
        <li id="li_rbl_cgk_54b">Start <ph keyref="product"/> and open a <term>DITA map</term><ph
            product="author editor authorEclipse editorEclipse"> in the <xref
              href="dita-maps-manager.dita#dita-maps-manager"><uicontrol>DITA Maps
                Manager</uicontrol> view</xref></ph>.</li>
        <li id="li_sbl_cgk_54b">Click the <uicontrol><image id="image_d3c_lxq_vr"
              href="../img/TransformConfig16.png"/>Configure Transformation Scenario(s)</uicontrol>
          button.</li>
        <li id="li_tbl_cgk_54b">Select the <uicontrol>DITA Map EPUB</uicontrol> transformation and
          click the <uicontrol>Edit</uicontrol> button to edit it. </li>
        <li>Run the transformation scenario and produce the EPUB.</li>
        <li>Install the Amazon <xref
            href="https://www.amazon.com/Kindle-Previewer/b?ie=UTF8&amp;node=21381691011"
            format="html" scope="external">Kindle Previewer</xref> utility and use it to produce a
          Kindle book from the EPUB.</li>
      </ol></p>
  </body>
</topic>
